JANUARY 1996

Product Award to
Digital Instruments

Digital Instruments (520 E. Montecito St., Santa Barbara, CA 93103,
Tel: 805/899-3380, Fax: 805/899-3392) received the prestigious
National New Product Award by the National Society of Professional
Engineers for the Scanning Probe Microscope tradenamed the
Dimension 7000.  The award will be presented to DI President Virgil
Elings.

According to the NSPE, "The award recognizes companies that are
developing innovative products and advancing technology through
outstanding engineering achievements.  They are given to the
creative minds that establish new products in the marketplace that
benefit the general public and the economy of California."

This is DI's first national award, after being honored by the
California Society of Professional Engineers for the best new
product in three of the last four years.  "This award is
particularly meaningful to us since it is voted on by our
engineering peers," said Elings.  DI's previous winners included
their original Atomic Force Microscope and the Large Sample Stage
SPM.




