January 1, 1996   

JAPAN TI SPONGE EXPORTS UP...

Japan's customs-cleared titanium sponge exports reached 574mt in November,
up 47.2% from 390mt in October and up 38% from 416mt in November 1994, the
Ministry of Finance reported. Exports to the US rose to 345mt, up 72.5%
from October's 200mt and 205% from 113mt a year ago. The November mean
export price to the US averaged Yen 825/kg ($3.68/lb) FOB in November, up
from Yen 722/kg ($3.25/lb) the previous month, and up from Yen 706/kg
($3.28/lb) a year earlier, MOF said. Japan's titanium sponge exports to the
European Union totaled 228mt in November, up 20% from 190mt in October, but
down 24.8% from 303mt in November 1994. Meanwhile, Japan's titanium sponge
exports during January-November reached 4,790mt, up 18.5% from 4,042mt for
the same period a year earlier. Exports to the US rose 30.4% to 1,490mt
from 1,143mt, and those to the EU increased to 3,136mt, up 8.7% from
2,884mt, MOF said.

