JUNE 1991

Surface Engineering Facilities Expanded

The Welding Institute (TWI) of Abington, United Kingdom, has added
a high velocity oxy-fuel system and a sol-gel laboratory to its
surface engineering facilities.

According to TWI, these additions will help it to provide
additional services to industry for both ceramics and metal matrix
composites, as well as metals.

Other surface engineering services currently located at TWI include
friction and laser surfacing, electron beam transformation
hardening, and arc spraying for coatings.

For further information contact The Welding Institute, Abington
Hall, Abington, Cambridgeshire CB1 6AL, United Kingdom.



