stimulating implications has applications in osteoporosis. The
condition affects more than 200 million people worldwide but numbers
are expected to escalate with the growth of the ageing population over
the next 25 to 35 years. The company also reports satisfactory outcomes
to Phase I/II clinical trials of NPS R-568 Norcalcin its
hyperparathyroidism treatment. The drug, licensed to Kirin Brewery Co
for Asia and to Amgen for the rest of the world, mimics the action of
calcium in activating the calcium receptor, reducing secretion of
parathyroid hormone and lowering levels of serum calcium.



