N. KOREA EVENTUALLY TO TAKE REFORM POLICY+

     SEOUL, DEC. 23 KYODO - ROMANIAN PRESIDENT NICOLAE CEAUSESCU'S
DOWNFALL EVENTUALLY WILL HELP ENCOURAGE REFORMS IN NORTH KOREA,
YONHAP NEWS AGENCY SAID ON SATURDAY.
     NORTH KOREA, WHICH HAS MAINTAINED CLOSE LINKS WITH ROMANIA, WILL
FACE SERIOUS ISOLATION IN THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY, YONHAP SAID,
QUOTING AN UNIDENTIFIED GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL.
     IT SAID NORTH KOREA IS EXPECTED TO TRY REFORM AND OPEN-DOOR
POLICIES, INITIALLY IN THE AREA OF ECONOMIC.



