CHINA TO GIVE AID, MAINTAIN FRIENDLY TIES WITH ROMANIA+

     BEIJING, DEC. 26 KYODO - CHINA IS READY TO MAINTAIN FRIENDLY
TIES WITH ROMANIA AND EXTEND HUMANITARIAN AID IN THE WAKE OF A BLOODY
UPRISING THAT ENDED THE 24-YEAR DICTATORSHIP OF NICOLAE CEAUSESCU,
CHINA'S DEPUTY FOREIGN MINISTER TIAN ZENGPEI SAID TUESDAY.
     CHINA'S POLICY TOWARD ROMANIA FOLLOWING THE EXECUTION MONDAY OF
ROMANIAN PRESIDENT CEAUSESCU, A FORMER STAUNCH ALLY OF CHINA, WILL
CONTINUE TO BE BASED ON THE PRINCIPLES OF PEACEFUL COEXISTENCE, THE
OFFICIAL XINHUA NEWS AGENCY QUOTED TIAN AS SAYING.
     THE CHINESE RED CROSS WILL PROVIDE EMERGENCY AID TO ROMANIA,
TIAN WAS ALSO QUOTED AS SAYING IN A MEETING WITH ANGELO MICULESCU,
ROMANIA'S AMBASSADOR TO BEIJING, THE AGENCY SAID.
     TIAN TOLD THE AMBASSADOR THAT THE CHINESE PEOPLE HAVE CHERISHED
THEIR FRIENDLY TIES WITH ROMANIANS AND RESPECT THEIR FREEDOM OF
CHOICE.
     THE CHINESE FOREIGN MINISTRY ALSO ISSUED A STATEMENT EARLIER IN
THE DAY SAYING THAT CHINA WILL NOT INTERFERE IN ROMANIA'S INTERNAL
AFFAIRS.



