Japan on Jan. 4, a top government spokesman said Thursday.
     ''There are various arguments against visiting Yasukuni Shrine,
but prime ministers' visits to Ise have already become a customary
annual event,'' Chief Cabinet Secretary Koken Nosaka told a press
conference.
